        "description": "<p>This plugin enhances WordPress REST API v2 responses about metadata.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload &#8220;rest-api-custom-fields&#8221; folder to the &#8220;/wp-content/plugins/&#8221; directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8220;Plugins&#8221; menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>New item &#8220;REST API Custom Fields&#8221; appears in the admin menu (under the Settings menu). There you can select which metadata you want to contain in the REST API response.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>It is now possible to expose custom fields of custom post types</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Exposed values can now contain arrays</li>\n<li>Attributes representing custom fields moved directly under the top-level node in the response</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed db prefix</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Init version</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
